</div> 
<p><strong>Pulley Crossbow</strong>&nbsp;is a <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Crossbows" href="/Crossbows" target="">Crossbow</a>&nbsp;in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Wiki" href="/Elden+Ring+Wiki">Elden Ring</a>. The <strong>Pulley Crossbow</strong> does not scale with any stat attributes, but requires <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Strength" href="/Strength" target="">Strength</a> and <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Dexterity" href="/Dexterity" target="">Dexterity</a>. It&nbsp;is a good <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Weapons" href="/Weapons" target="">Weapon</a> for those users who prefer to fight their battles from afar. The <strong>Crossbow Pulley</strong> ability allows players to push <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Enemies" href="/Enemies" target="">Enemies</a>&nbsp;back with a high kick.</p> 
<p>The Pulley Crossbow fires three bolts with one press of the trigger, with a slight spread between bolts.</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<div class="lineleft"> 
 <p><em>Crossbow made with pulleys and power springs. The complex mechanism, which required advanced mathematical and mechanical understanding to craft, was likely made by a certain genius who learned Golden Order fundamentalism.&nbsp;<br></em></p> 
 <p><em>One touch fires a volley of bolts. Be warned; large stores of bolts can be quickly spent.</em></p> 
</div> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Where to Find Pulley Crossbow in&nbsp;Elden Ring</h3> 
<p>The Pulley Crossbow weapon can be found at the following location:</p> 
<ul> 
 <li>Found next to the Site of Grace at the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Craftsman's Shack" href="/Craftsman's+Shack">Craftsman's Shack</a>. [<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Interactive Map?id=5827&amp;lat=-94.257103&amp;lng=65.894893&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA" href="/Interactive+Map?id=5827&amp;lat=-94.257103&amp;lng=65.894893&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA">Elden Ring Map here</a>]</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Elden Ring Pulley Crossbow Notes &amp; Tips</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Weapon <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Skills" href="/Skills" target="">Skill</a>: <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Kick" href="/Kick" target="">Kick</a></li> 
 <li>This weapon fires its bolts with an unusually large upward pitch (tilt). When aiming at mid-range, players should aim&nbsp;lower than usual, aiming at humanoid enemies' chests to land headshots</li> 
 <li>Due to the this weapon's reliance on multiplicity of shots over a single, powerful shot,&nbsp;landing headshots against low-pose creatures, especially those upright (humanoids etc.), it is often extremely difficult to&nbsp;land&nbsp;all the weapon's shots against the enemy's head, due to their flinch and hurt animations.</li> 
 <li>This weapon&nbsp;cannot be infused with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Ashes of War" href="/Ashes+of+War" target="">Ashes of War</a>.</li> 
 <li><strong>Pulley Crossbow</strong> can be upgraded by using <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Somber Smithing Stones" href="/Somber+Smithing+Stones">Somber Smithing Stones</a></li> 
 <li>Sell Value:&nbsp;&nbsp;<img title="Runes" src="/file/Elden-Ring/er-runes-13.png" alt="er runes 13" width="18" height="18">&nbsp;100</li> 
 <li><span style="text-decoration: line-through;">Due to a bug, when used 1-handed in offhand, this weapon applies any elemental/status buff (spell buff, weapon skill buff, grease) from mainhand weapon.</span><br>(Fixed in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Patch Notes" href="/Patch+Notes">patch 1.05</a>).</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Moveset &amp; Videos in&nbsp;Elden Ring for&nbsp;Pulley Crossbow</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Videos for the Pulley Crossbow Coming Soon</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Pulley Crossbow Upgrades in Elden Ring</h3> 
<p>Please see the&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Upgrades" href="/Upgrades" target="">Upgrades</a>&nbsp;page to understand the weapon bolstering process.</p> 
<p>Requires regular reinforcement with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Somber Smithing Stones" href="/Somber+Smithing+Stones" target="">Somber Smithing Stones</a></p> 
<p>This upgrade can't be enchanted with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Magic Spells" href="/Magic+Spells" target="">Magic</a> nor boosted with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Consumables" href="/Consumables" target="">Consumables</a>.</p> 
